section.def:
promisee (受諾人), in
            relation to a term of a contract enforceable by a third party under section
            4, means a party to the contract who may enforce the term against the promisor;

promisor (許諾人), in
            relation to a term of a contract enforceable by a third party under section
            4, means a party to the contract against whom a third party may enforce the term;

paragraph.content:
a company’s articles having effect as a contract under seal under
                        section 86 of the Companies Ordinance (Cap. 622);
                    (Amended 16 of 2016 s. 47)

subsection.def:
negotiable instrument (可流轉票據) includes any instrument embodying a monetary
                obligation and transferable by delivery, or by delivery and indorsement, whether or
                not the instrument is capable of being transferred free from equities;
